<br>
By Milrop <br>
Becoming a Master Potter is not difficult. The single best spot to train in this tradeskill is Thurgadin. You have the bank, the vendors, pottery wheel and kiln all in the same building! The water vendor is not too far either. If you need to make metal bits, that can be done in Thurgadin as well. Well, here is my recommended guide to getting to Master Potter level. <br>
<br>
1. Start out by making Small Clay Jars. Do this until you get to skill 31. <br>
<br>
Materials to combine in Pottery Wheel: <br>
a block of clay <br>
small jar sketch <br>
flask of water <br>
If you get an unfired jar, you can combine it and a quality firing sheet in the kiln to make the final product. <br>
<br>
2. Go to Large Clay Jars next. Do this until you get to skill 41. <br>
<br>
Materials to combine in Pottery Wheel: <br>
a block of clay <br>
large jar sketch <br>
flask of water <br>
If you get an unfired jar, you can combine it and a quality firing sheet in the kiln to make the final product. <br>
<br>
3. Make a Pot. This will get you to skill 56. You will need to have metal bits made to do this. I recommend doing the pot because you can actually get a good price from these at times from people doing the Coldain Prayer Shawl quest. They need a pot for one of the baking steps. <br>
<br>
Materials to combine in Pottery Wheel: <br>
a large block of clay <br>
pot sketch <br>
metal bit (2 Small pieces of ore + Flask of water combined in a Forge) <br>
flask of water <br>
If you get an unfired pot, you can combine it and a high quality firing sheet in the kiln to make the final product. <br>
<br>
4. Make Small Bowls. This will get you to skill 102. <br>
<br>
Materials to combine in Pottery Wheel: <br>
a small block of clay <br>
bowl sketch <br>
flask of water <br>
If you get an unfired bowl, you can combine it and a high quality firing sheet in the kiln to make the final product. <br>
<br>
You are now a Master Potter! The cost is very minimal (especially when compared to other trade skills). There are some nice items that can be made too. I will add a couple recipies below. A good site to visit is <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtradeskills.com/pottery.htm.">www.eqtradeskills.com/pottery.htm.</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
- Pie Tin. This is needed for the Coldain Prayer Shawl quest. You may be able to make a profit from people needing it for the quest. <br>
<br>
Materials to combine in Pottery Wheel: <br>
2 blocks of clay <br>
pie tin sketch <br>
flask of water <br>
If you get an unfired bowl, you can combine it and a high quality firing sheet in the kiln to make the final product. <br>
<br>
- Mixing Bowl. Again, this is needed for people doing the Coldain Prayer Shawl quest. <br>
<br>
Materials to combine in Pottery Wheel: <br>
2 large blocks of clay <br>
mixing bowl sketch <br>
flask of water <br>
If you get an unfired bowl, you can combine it and a firing sheet in the kiln to make the final product. <br>
<br>
- Thurgadin Gate Potion (used in step 4 of the Coldain Prayer Shawl quest, works for anyone). You will have to go to Crystal Caverns to gather necessary materials first. <br>
<br>
Materials to combine in Pottery Wheel: <br>
a small brick of velium (7 pound one) <br>
3 unstacked Crystalline Silks <br>
2 glass shards <br>
If you get an unfired vial, you can combine it and a high quality firing sheet in the kiln to make the finished vial. <br>
<br>
If you get a Velium Vial, then go find Frundle Frenkler (lady coldain in potion shop). Ask her, &quot;what velium vapors&quot;. She will give you an item for you to combine your new vial and 2 small pieces of velium. This will give you the gate potion. <br>
<br>
